  "type": "mcq",
  "stem": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The measure of angle <math alttext=\"upper Z\"><mi>Z</mi>\n</math> is <math alttext=\"60 degree\"><mn>60</mn>\n<mo>&#176;</mo></math>. What is the measure, in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">radians</span>, of angle <math alttext=\"upper Z\"><mi>Z</mi>\n</math>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "4c476f55-9a00-47e0-985d-4447a0897089",
      "content": "<p><math alttext=\"one sixth pi\"><mfrac>\n\t<mn>1</mn>\n\t<mn>6</mn>\n</mfrac>\n<mi>&#960;</mi></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "823450aa-e3a7-4ba0-bb14-b3e145be225d",
      "content": "<p><math alttext=\"one third pi\"><mfrac>\n\t<mn>1</mn>\n\t<mn>3</mn>\n</mfrac>\n<mi>&#960;</mi></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "59e09358-fe35-43c5-85be-e17177f05d34",
      "content": "<p><math alttext=\"two thirds pi\"><mfrac>\n\t<mn>2</mn>\n\t<mn>3</mn>\n</mfrac>\n<mi>&#960;</mi></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "8404fd1a-795e-4596-91e4-16c6474dc3b1",
      "content": "<p><math alttext=\"1 pi\"><mn>1</mn>\n<mi>&#960;</mi></math></p>"
    }
  ],
  "keys": [
    "823450aa-e3a7-4ba0-bb14-b3e145be225d"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is correct. The measure of an angle, in radians, can be found by multiplying its measure, in degrees, by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"StartFraction pi Over 180 EndFraction\"><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>180</mn></mfrac></math>. It's given that the measure of angle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper Z\"><mi>Z</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"60 degree\"><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>. It follows that&nbsp;the measure, in radians, of angle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper Z\"><mi>Z</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"60 left parenthesis StartFraction pi Over 180 EndFraction right parenthesis\"><mn>60</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>180</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"one third pi\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is incorrect. This is the measure, in radians, of an angle whose measure is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"30 degree\"><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>, not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"60 degree\"><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is incorrect. This is the measure, in radians, of an angle whose measure is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"120 degree\"><mn>120</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>, not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"60 degree\"><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice D is incorrect. This is the measure, in radians, of an angle whose measure is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"180 degree\"><mn>180</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>, not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"60 degree\"><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>.</p>",
